headline: How McDonald's (MCD) Dividend Hike Signals Confidence in Cash Flow and Growth Strategy
summary: On October 22, 2025, McDonald's Corporation announced a 5% increase in its quarterly cash dividend to US$1.86 per share, payable on December 15, 2025, for shareholders of record as of December 1, 2025. This higher dividend underscores the company's confidence in its Accelerating the Arches growth strategy and commitment to long-term shareholder returns. We'll examine how McDonald’s increased dividend signals ongoing strength in free cash flow and reinforces confidence in future earnings...
